article.headline: Wichita St. 87, Alcorn St. 52
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. -- Aaron Ellis scored a season-high 14 points to lead Wichita State to an 87-52 victory over Alcorn State on Monday night. Garrett Stutz had 10 points and 12 rebounds for the Shockers (5-1), who shot 51.7 percent from inside the 3-point line. Alcorn State (0-9) was led JaMarkus Holt's 13 points. The Shockers blazed to a 10-2 lead behind Ellis, who topped his previous season high of 10 points before halftime. Alcorn State got back into the game briefly, cutting the gap to 18-14 on Michael Starks' tip-in with 9:50 remaining in the half. But the Braves, playing their ninth straight road game, made only one basket in the next nine minutes and had 19 first-half turnovers. That allowed the Shockers to take control, cruising to a 42-24 halftime advantage. Wichita State started the second half with a 15-2 run and led by as many as 33.
